Going by the long procession, many residents of Meru town assumed that it was the wedding party of a stinking rich couple. But they were wrong.This was a celebration alright, but of a different kind; Mr Zabron Mathege was celebrating the arrival of his new vehicle, a Hummer H3 limousine, said to be worth a cool Sh40 million. It was a spectacle to behold that made business people to hastily shutter their shops to have a glimpse of the&nbsp;marvel from USA.All boda boda riders had been requested to suspend their business and escort the limo to the celebration venue at Kaaga Primary.&nbsp;However, the riders did not go home empty-handed as the deep-pocketed Mathege gave them Sh1,000 each for joining in the party.